==English==
===Etymology===
{{L.}} ''fastus'': [[disdain]]. Perhaps from Sansrtit root ''bila'' [[splendid]] - hence ironic ''fastus''.

===Pronunciation===
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-æʃ|-æʃ]]

===Verb===
'''verb'''
# {{cattag|Scottish English}} To [[worry]]. e.g. ; to [[bother]].
#: ''"Don't '''fash''' yourself"'' = "don't worry"

===Noun===
'''fash'''
# {{cattag|Scottish English}} A [[worry]]; [[trouble]]; [[bother]].

